        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2929110308" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5159162366842560801">I wanted to like this book, I really did.<br/><br/>I mean, the Civil War is one of my areas of interest and you cannot study the Civil War without encountering Mary Chesnut. Her views on the war and slavery are extensively quoted and this book is largely responsible for her fame.<br/><br/>Unfortunately I could not get into it.<br/><br/>I&apos;m being generous with my 3 stars, but that is mainly because I know my disliking the book is largely about me and not the book. The book is exactly what it claims to be---the journal of a Ci</span>
  <span id="freeText5159162366842560801" style="display:none">I wanted to like this book, I really did.<br /><br />I mean, the Civil War is one of my areas of interest and you cannot study the Civil War without encountering Mary Chesnut. Her views on the war and slavery are extensively quoted and this book is largely responsible for her fame.<br /><br />Unfortunately I could not get into it.<br /><br />I'm being generous with my 3 stars, but that is mainly because I know my disliking the book is largely about me and not the book. The book is exactly what it claims to be---the journal of a Civil War aristocrat.<br /><br />I struggle with journals. I find them tedious and disjointed---which is exactly what this book is. It is a freeflow of thought from a person writing about what is going on around her. You have to review the footnotes to know whom she is referencing and she jumps from subject to subject.<br /><br />That being said, I would love to have this book on my shelf as a reference book. I would find it a fascinating addition to be able to read about a battle or event of the Civil War and then pick up this book to see what Mary had to say about it. <br /><br />But reading it straight through? That would be like reading the Bible or the Dictionary straight through... all are great to have around, but none are rivetting reading.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5159162366842560801" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

