  <span id="freeText12707869252765076996" style="display:none">It is a diary worth reading, but don't forget, it is a diary. It was like peeking into someone's private letters. The insight into the mind and perspective of the slave owning 1% was neither surprising nor uplifting. Mary Chestnut validates the expression "educated but stupid."Mr. Woodward deserves all the appropriate accolades for presenting this as he did. It is a must-have and must-read for anyone interested in the 19th century and specifically the civil war. The reader has an opportunity to know the mind behind the sweet southern charm and petal soft hand pressing against the back of of the soldiers, encouraging them to noble deaths and wasted lives.</span>
