      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cheryl" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cheryl" href="/user/show/5548641-cheryl">Cheryl</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2431509065" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3608601438295923392">A tough go. The author researched the work of Chesnut in great detail and supplied a lot of supporting material that certainly clarified her writing. But, the period vernacular, Chesnut’s idiosyncratic writing style and the sheer volume of her journal made it very difficult for me to follow. Still, it was a fascinating glimpse into the Southern experience of the Civil War.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


